4 Operational behavior -> 4.12 Enhanced:
{
    "4 Operational behavior -> 4.12 Enhanced authentication": [
        {
            "Original": "The MQTT CONNECT packet supports basic authentication of a Network Connection using the User Name and Password fields.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "While these fields are named for a simple password authentication, they can be used to carry other forms of authentication such as passing a token as the Password.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Enhanced authentication extends this basic authentication to include challenge / response style authentication.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "It might involve the exchange of AUTH packets between the Client and the Server after the CONNECT and before the CONNACK packets.",
            "Adjusted": "Enhanced authentication might involve the exchange of AUTH packets between the Client and the Server after the CONNECT and before the CONNACK packets."
        },
        {
            "Original": "To begin an enhanced authentication, the Client includes an Authentication Method in the CONNECT packet.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "This specifies the authentication method to use.",
            "Adjusted": "The Authentication Method specifies the authentication method to use."
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the Server does not support the Authentication Method supplied by the Client, it MAY send a CONNACK with a Reason Code of 0x8C (Bad authentication method) or 0x87 (Not Authorized) as described in section 4.13 and MUST close the Network Connection [MQTT-4.12.0-1].",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The Authentication Method is an agreement between the Client and Server about the meaning of the data sent in the Authentication Data and any of the other fields in CONNECT, and the exchanges and processing needed by the Client and Server to complete the authentication.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "**Non-normative comment** The Authentication Method is commonly a SASL mechanism, and using such a registered name aids interchange.",
            "Adjusted": "The Authentication Method is commonly a SASL mechanism, and using such a registered name aids interchange."
        },
        {
            "Original": "However, the Authentication Method is not constrained to using registered SASL mechanisms.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the Authentication Method selected by the Client specifies that the Client sends data first, the Client SHOULD include an Authentication Data property in the CONNECT packet.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "This property can be used to provide data as specified by the Authentication Method.",
            "Adjusted": "The Authentication Data property can be used to provide data as specified by the Authentication Method."
        },
        {
            "Original": "The contents of the Authentication Data are defined by the authentication method.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the Server requires additional information to complete the authentication, it can send an AUTH packet to the Client.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "This packet MUST contain a Reason Code of 0x18 (Continue authentication) [MQTT-4.12.0-2].",
            "Adjusted": "The AUTH packet MUST contain a Reason Code of 0x18 (Continue authentication) [MQTT-4.12.0-2]."
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the authentication method requires the Server to send authentication data to the Client, it is sent in the Authentication Data.",
            "Adjusted": "If the authentication method requires the Server to send authentication data to the Client, the data is sent in the Authentication Data."
        },
        {
            "Original": "The Client responds to an AUTH packet from the Server by sending a further AUTH packet.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "This packet MUST contain a Reason Code of 0x18 (Continue authentication) [MQTT-4.12.0-3].",
            "Adjusted": "The AUTH packet MUST contain a Reason Code of 0x18 (Continue authentication) [MQTT-4.12.0-3]."
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the authentication method requires the Client to send authentication data for the Server, it is sent in the Authentication Data.",
            "Adjusted": "If the authentication method requires the Client to send authentication data for the Server, the data is sent in the Authentication Data."
        },
        {
            "Original": "The Client and Server exchange AUTH packets as needed until the Server accepts the authentication by sending a CONNACK with a Reason Code of 0.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the acceptance of the authentication requires data to be sent to the Client, it is sent in the Authentication Data.",
            "Adjusted": "If the acceptance of the authentication requires data to be sent to the Client, the data is sent in the Authentication Data."
        },
        {
            "Original": "The Client can close the connection at any point in this process.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "It MAY send a DISCONNECT packet before doing so.",
            "Adjusted": "The Client MAY send a DISCONNECT packet before closing the connection."
        },
        {
            "Original": "The Server can reject the authentication at any point in this process.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "It MAY send a CONNACK with a Reason Code of 0x80 or above as described in section 4.13, and MUST close the Network Connection [MQTT-4.12.0-4].",
            "Adjusted": "The Server MAY send a CONNACK with a Reason Code of 0x80 or above as described in section 4.13, and MUST close the Network Connection [MQTT-4.12.0-4]."
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the initial CONNECT packet included an Authentication Method property then all AUTH packets, and any successful CONNACK packet MUST include an Authentication Method Property with the same value as in the CONNECT packet [MQTT-4.12.0-5].",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The implementation of enhanced authentication is OPTIONAL for both Clients and Servers.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the Client does not include an Authentication Method in the CONNECT, the Server MUST NOT send an AUTH packet, and it MUST NOT send an Authentication Method in the CONNACK packet [MQTT-4.12.0-6].",
            "Adjusted": "If the Client does not include an Authentication Method in the CONNECT, the Server MUST NOT send an AUTH packet, and the Server MUST NOT send an Authentication Method in the CONNACK packet [MQTT-4.12.0-6]."
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the Client does not include an Authentication Method in the CONNECT, the Client MUST NOT send an AUTH packet to the Server [MQTT-4.12.0-7].",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the Client does not include an Authentication Method in the CONNECT packet, the Server SHOULD authenticate using some or all of the information in the CONNECT packet, TLS session, and Network Connection.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "**** **Non-normative example showing a SCRAM challenge****** Client to Server: CONNECT Authentication Method=\"SCRAM-SHA-1\" Authentication Data=client-first-data Server to Client: AUTH rc=0x18 Authentication Method=\"SCRAM-SHA-1\" Authentication Data=server-first-data Client to Server AUTH rc=0x18 Authentication Method=\"SCRAM-SHA-1\" Authentication Data=client-final-data Server to Client CONNACK rc=0 Authentication Method=\"SCRAM-SHA-1\" Authentication Data=server-final-data **Non-normative example showing a Kerberos challenge****** Client to Server CONNECT Authentication Method=\"GS2-KRB5\" Server to Client AUTH rc=0x18 Authentication Method=\"GS2-KRB5\" Client to Server AUTH rc=0x18 Authentication Method=\"GS2-KRB5\" Authentication Data=initial context token Server to Client AUTH rc=0x18 Authentication Method=\"GS2-KRB5\" Authentication Data=reply context token Client to Server AUTH rc=0x18 Authentication Method=\"GS2-KRB5\" Server to Client CONNACK rc=0 Authentication Method=\"GS2-KRB5\" Authentication Data=outcome of authentication",
            "Adjusted": "Non-normative example showing a SCRAM challenge: Client to Server: CONNECT Authentication Method=\"SCRAM-SHA-1\" Authentication Data=client-first-data Server to Client: AUTH rc=0x18 Authentication Method=\"SCRAM-SHA-1\" Authentication Data=server-first-data Client to Server: AUTH rc=0x18 Authentication Method=\"SCRAM-SHA-1\" Authentication Data=client-final-data Server to Client: CONNACK rc=0 Authentication Method=\"SCRAM-SHA-1\" Authentication Data=server-final-data. Non-normative example showing a Kerberos challenge: Client to Server: CONNECT Authentication Method=\"GS2-KRB5\" Server to Client: AUTH rc=0x18 Authentication Method=\"GS2-KRB5\" Client to Server: AUTH rc=0x18 Authentication Method=\"GS2-KRB5\" Authentication Data=initial context token Server to Client: AUTH rc=0x18 Authentication Method=\"GS2-KRB5\" Authentication Data=reply context token Client to Server: AUTH rc=0x18 Authentication Method=\"GS2-KRB5\" Server to Client: CONNACK rc=0 Authentication Method=\"GS2-KRB5\" Authentication Data=outcome of authentication"
        }
    ]
}

4 Operational behavior -> 4.8 Subscripti:
{
    "4 Operational behavior -> 4.8 Subscriptions -> 4.8.2 Shared Subscriptions": [
        {
            "Original": "A Shared Subscription can be associated with multiple subscribing MQTT Sessions.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Like a Non-shared Subscription, it has a Topic Filter and Subscription Options; however, a publication that matches its Topic Filter is only sent to one of its subscribing Sessions.",
            "Adjusted": "Like a Non-shared Subscription, a Shared Subscription has a Topic Filter and Subscription Options; however, a publication that matches the Shared Subscription's Topic Filter is only sent to one of its subscribing Sessions."
        },
        {
            "Original": "Shared Subscriptions are useful where several consuming Clients share the processing of the publications in parallel.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "A Shared Subscription is identified using a special style of Topic Filter.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The format of this filter is: share/{ShareName}/{filter} share is a literal string that marks the Topic Filter as being a Shared Subscription Topic Filter.",
            "Adjusted": "The format of this filter is: share/{ShareName}/{filter}. The string 'share' is a literal string that marks the Topic Filter as being a Shared Subscription Topic Filter."
        },
        {
            "Original": "{ShareName} is a character string that does not include \"/\", \"+\" or \"#\" {filter} The remainder of the string has the same syntax and semantics as a Topic Filter in a non-shared subscription.",
            "Adjusted": "{ShareName} is a character string that does not include \"/\", \"+\" or \"#\". {filter} is the remainder of the string and has the same syntax and semantics as a Topic Filter in a non-shared subscription."
        },
        {
            "Original": "Refer to section 4.7.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "A Shared Subscription's Topic Filter MUST start with share/ and MUST contain a ShareName that is at least one character long [MQTT-4.8.2-1].",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The ShareName MUST NOT contain the characters \"/\", \"+\" or \"#\", but MUST be followed by a \"/\" character.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "This \"/\" character MUST be followed by a Topic Filter [MQTT-4.8.2-2] as described in section 4.7.",
            "Adjusted": "The \"/\" character after the ShareName MUST be followed by a Topic Filter [MQTT-4.8.2-2] as described in section 4.7."
        },
        {
            "Original": "**Non-normative comment** Shared Subscriptions are defined at the scope of the MQTT Server, rather than of a Session.",
            "Adjusted": "Shared Subscriptions are defined at the scope of the MQTT Server, rather than of a Session."
        },
        {
            "Original": "A ShareName is included in the Shared Subscription's Topic Filter so that there can be more than one Shared Subscription on a Server that has the same {filter} component.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Typically, applications use the ShareName to represent the group of subscribing Sessions that are sharing the subscription.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Examples: Shared subscriptions \"share/consumer1/sport/tennis/+\" and \"share/consumer2/sport/tennis/+\" are distinct shared subscriptions and so can be associated with different groups of Sessions.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Both of them match the same topics as a non-shared subscription to sport/tennis/+ .",
            "Adjusted": "Both of these Shared Subscriptions match the same topics as a non-shared subscription to sport/tennis/+."
        },
        {
            "Original": "If a message were to be published that matches sport/tennis/+ then a copy would be sent to exactly one of the Sessions subscribed to share/consumer1/sport/tennis/+ , a separate copy of the message would be sent to exactly one of the Sessions subscribed to share/consumer2/sport/tennis/+ and further copies would be sent to any Clients with non-shared subscriptions to sport/tennis/+ Shared subscription \"share/consumer1//finance\" matches the same topics as a non-shared subscription to /finance.",
            "Adjusted": "If a message were to be published that matches sport/tennis/+, then a copy would be sent to exactly one of the Sessions subscribed to share/consumer1/sport/tennis/+, a separate copy of the message would be sent to exactly one of the Sessions subscribed to share/consumer2/sport/tennis/+, and further copies would be sent to any Clients with non-shared subscriptions to sport/tennis/+. Shared subscription \"share/consumer1//finance\" matches the same topics as a non-shared subscription to /finance."
        },
        {
            "Original": "A Shared Subscription is created by using a Shared Subscription Topic Filter in a SUBSCRIBE request.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "So long as only one Session subscribes to a particular Shared Subscription, the shared subscription behaves like a non-shared subscription, except that: The share and {ShareName} portions of the Topic Filter are not taken into account when matching against publications.",
            "Adjusted": "So long as only one Session subscribes to a particular Shared Subscription, the shared subscription behaves like a non-shared subscription, except that the share and {ShareName} portions of the Topic Filter are not taken into account when matching against publications."
        },
        {
            "Original": "No Retained Messages are sent to the Session when it first subscribes.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "It will be sent other matching messages as they are published.",
            "Adjusted": "The Session will be sent other matching messages as they are published."
        },
        {
            "Original": "Once a Shared Subscription exists, it is possible for other Sessions to subscribe with the same Shared Subscription Topic Filter.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The new Session is associated with the Shared Subscription as an additional subscriber.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Retained messages are not sent to this new subscriber.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Each subsequent Application Message that matches the Shared Subscription is now sent to one and only one of the Sessions that are subscribed to the Shared Subscription.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "A Session can explicitly detach itself from a Shared Subscription by sending an UNSUBSCRIBE Packet that contains the full Shared Subscription Topic Filter.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Sessions are also detached from the Shared Subscription when they terminate.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "A Shared Subscription lasts for as long as it is associated with at least one Session (i.e.",
            "Adjusted": "A Shared Subscription lasts for as long as it is associated with at least one Session."
        },
        {
            "Original": "a Session that has issued a successful SUBSCRIBE request to its Topic Filter and that has not completed a corresponding UNSUBSCRIBE).",
            "Adjusted": "This means a Session that has issued a successful SUBSCRIBE request to its Topic Filter and that has not completed a corresponding UNSUBSCRIBE."
        },
        {
            "Original": "A Shared Subscription survives when the Session that originally created it unsubscribes, unless there are no other Sessions left when this happens.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "A Shared Subscription ends, and any undelivered messages associated with it are deleted, when there are no longer any Sessions subscribed to it.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Notes on Shared Subscriptions If there's more than one Session subscribed to the Shared Subscription, the Server implementation is free to choose, on a message by message basis, which Session to use and what criteria it uses to make this selection.",
            "Adjusted": "If there's more than one Session subscribed to the Shared Subscription, the Server implementation is free to choose, on a message by message basis, which Session to use and what criteria it uses to make this selection."
        },
        {
            "Original": "Different subscribing Clients are permitted to ask for different Requested QoS levels in their SUBSCRIBE packets.",
