        },
        {
            "Original": "The Server decides which Maximum QoS to grant to each Client, and it is permitted to grant different Maximum QoS levels to different subscribers.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "When sending an Application Message to a Client, the Server MUST respect the granted QoS for the Client's subscription [MQTT-4.8.2-3], in the same that it does when sending a message to a -Subscriber.",
            "Adjusted": "When sending an Application Message to a Client, the Server MUST respect the granted QoS for the Client's subscription [MQTT-4.8.2-3], in the same way that it does when sending a message to a Subscriber."
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the Server is in the process of sending a QoS 2 message to its chosen subscribing Client and the connection to the Client breaks before delivery is complete, the Server MUST complete the delivery of the message to that Client when it reconnects [MQTT-4.8.2-4] as described in section 4.3.3.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the Client's Session terminates before the Client reconnects, the Server MUST NOT send the Application Message to any other subscribed Client [MQTT-4.8.2-5].",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the Server is in the process of sending a QoS 1 message to its chosen subscribing Client and the connection to that Client breaks before the Server has received an acknowledgement from the Client, the Server MAY wait for the Client to reconnect and retransmit the message to that Client.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the Client'sSession terminates before the Client reconnects, the Server SHOULD send the Application Message to another Client that is subscribed to the same Shared Subscription.",
            "Adjusted": "If the Client's Session terminates before the Client reconnects, the Server SHOULD send the Application Message to another Client that is subscribed to the same Shared Subscription."
        },
        {
            "Original": "It MAY attempt to send the message to another Client as soon as it loses its connection to the first Client.",
            "Adjusted": "The Server MAY attempt to send the message to another Client as soon as it loses its connection to the first Client."
        },
        {
            "Original": "If a Client responds with a PUBACK or PUBREC containing a Reason Code of 0x80 or greater to a PUBLISH packet from the Server, the Server MUST discard the Application Message and not attempt to send it to any other Subscriber [MQTT-4.8.2-6].",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "A Client is permitted to submit a second SUBSCRIBE request to a Shared Subscription on a Session that's already subscribed to that Shared Subscription.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "For example, it might do this to change the Requested QoS for its subscription or because it was uncertain that the previous subscribe completed before the previous connection was closed.",
            "Adjusted": "For example, the Client might do this to change the Requested QoS for its subscription or because it was uncertain that the previous subscribe completed before the previous connection was closed."
        },
        {
            "Original": "This does not increase the number of times that the Session is associated with the Shared Subscription, so the Session will leave the Shared Subscription on its first UNSUBSCRIBE.",
